---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Raga Bhairavi — Complete Lesson | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Master Raga Bhairavi — India's most beloved raga, the traditional concert finale. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Raga Bhairavi — Complete Lesson</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-intermediate capitalize">intermediate</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 40 min · Intermediate</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Raga Bhairavi — Complete Lesson</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Master Raga Bhairavi — India's most beloved raga, the traditional concert finale.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Uses komal Re Ga Dha Ni — most komal of any raga</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Aroha: S r g M P d n upper-S</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Vadi: Ma — emphasized throughout</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Traditionally performed as the last piece of any concert</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Rasa: Karuna (compassion) — deeply emotional</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>Why Bhairavi is Special</h2>
      <p>Raga Bhairavi is perhaps the most universally loved raga in Indian music. It concludes every classical concert because no raga after Bhairavi can satisfy an audience. Its predominant use of komal Re Ga Dha and Ni gives it a tender emotional quality that speaks directly to the heart regardless of the listener's musical background.</p>

      <h2>Complete Profile</h2>
      <p>Thaat: Bhairavi. Jati: Sampurna. Aroha: S r g M P d n upper-S. Avaroha: upper-S n d P M g r S. Vadi: Ma. Samvadi: Sa. Time: Early morning and traditionally as concert finale at any time. Rasa: Karuna (tender compassion). Also uses Tivra Ma in some characteristic phrases adding emotional contrast.</p>

      <h2>Aroha and Avaroha Practice</h2>
      <p>Aroha keys: A W D F G Y U K. Avaroha keys: K U Y G F D W A. Notice almost every note is a black key (komal) except Sa Ma and Pa. This predominance of komal swaras creates Bhairavi's characteristic tender emotional color. Practice very slowly and listen to the difference each komal swara makes compared to its natural version.</p>

      <h2>Characteristic Phrases</h2>
      <p>Opening phrase: n S r g (gentle movement toward Sa). Most characteristic phrase: M g r S (descending from Ma with komal Ga and Re to Sa — this phrase is unmistakably Bhairavi). Wide descending sweep: n d P M g r S. Practice each of these phrases separately for 10 repetitions before combining them in free melodic exploration.</p>

      <h2>Simple Bhairavi Composition</h2>
      <p>Sthayi: S r g M comma P M g r S. Antara: d n upper-S comma upper-S n d P M g r S. This simple composition captures the essence of Bhairavi's tender emotional quality. Practice it very slowly — Bhairavi truly suffers when rushed. The slower and more deliberate your playing the more emotionally powerful the effect.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>